definitions.definition: To yield or give way to another.
definitions.example: They will not submit to the destruction of their rights.

definitions.definition: To yield (something) to another, as when defeated.
To enter or put forward for approval, consideration, marking etc.
definitions.example: I submit these plans for your approval.

definitions.definition: To subject; to put through a process.
(mixed martial arts) To win a fight against (an opponent) by submission.
